com.pump.io

Class IndentedPrintStream

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.io.OutputStream
      • java.io.FilterOutputStream
        • java.io.PrintStream
          • com.pump.io.IndentedPrintStream
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Closeable, java.io.Flushable, java.lang.Appendable, java.lang.AutoCloseable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ClassWriterStream

    public class IndentedPrintStream
extends java.io.PrintStream
    This PrintStream helps manage indentation when you invoke any print(x) or println(x) method.

    In addition to use indent() and unindent(), you can use the try-with-resources syntax so your code would resemble: 

     try(IndentedPrintStream ips = new IndentedPrintStream(out, true, "UTF-8")) {
        ips.println("Outer Text");
        try(AutoCloseable c = ips.indent()) {
                ips.println("Middle Text");
                try(AutoCloseable c2 = ips.indent()) {
                        ips.println("Inner Text");
                }
                ips.println("More Middle Text");
        }
        ips.println("More Outer Text");
}
